#topic 1 to 5
plot(prep, covariate="CI", topics = c(1), model=forfit, method = "continuous", xlab = "less cooperation ... more cooperation", main = "The Effects of Topics on Cooperation", labeltype = "custom", custom.labels = c("off-topic/socializing"))

plot(prep, covariate="CI", topics = c(2), model=forfit, method = "continuous", xlab = "less cooperation ... more cooperation", main = "The Effects of Topics on Cooperation", labeltype = "custom", custom.labels = c("evaluation of past rounds"))

plot(prep, covariate="CI", topics = c(3), model=forfit, method = "continuous", xlab = "less cooperation ... more cooperation", main = "The Effects of Topics on Cooperation", labeltype = "custom", custom.labels = c("coordination where to harvest"))

plot(prep, covariate="CI", topics = c(4), model=forfit, method = "continuous", xlab = "less cooperation ... more cooperation", main = "The Effects of Topics on Cooperation", labeltype = "custom", custom.labels = c("coordination when to harvest"))

plot(prep, covariate="CI", topics = c(5), model=forfit, method = "continuous", xlab = "less cooperation ... more cooperation", main = "The Effects of Topics on Cooperation", labeltype = "custom", custom.labels = c("off-topic/socializing"))

Interpreting results need caution. The estimated relationship is correlational not causational. Groups with little level of cooperation tends to talk more about coordination, but as they cooperate more effectively, they talk significantly less about coordination.
